title: Solving by Quadratic Formula
description: A series of problems on solving quadratic equations using the quadratic formula, covering identification of coefficients, discriminant calculation, and finding real or complex roots. All mathematical expressions are rendered using LaTeX.

questions.question: If $x^2 - 5x + 6 = 0$, identify the correct $a, b, c$ in $ax^2 + bx + c = 0$.
For $3t^2 - 12 = 0$, identify the correct $a, b, c$ in $ax^2 + bx + c = 0$.
Solve $x^2 - x - 12 = 0$ using the quadratic formula.
Solve $x^2 - 12 = x$ using the quadratic formula.
